Reposting from last year!

We're approaching the anniversary for Hurricane Katrina. Every year I fully immerse myself in all the information I possibly can find about it. 
Every year I find new things out, every year I sit in shock at how this tragedy was handled by our government. Last year I came across three very educational documentaries about Katrina on HBO Max. Spike Lee's 'When the Levees broke: A requiem in four acts'. Spike Lee's 'If God is Willing and Da Creek don't Rise'. And 'Katrina Babies'. 
The information I stumbled across was just mind-blowing, if you ever needed a reason to believe the government doesn't care about it's people. I highly recommend watching these documentaries!!

Happy Thanksgiving to all my favorite outcasts. 🦃🤎

10 years ago I would've spent my birthday weekend getting blackout drunk in some cheap bar that no longer exists.

 2 days shy of 31 years old me, spent my birthday weekend with some of the most wonderful humans giving back to those who need it most. 

Approximately 200 people or more, received a hot, home-cooked, traditional Thanksgiving meal, all thanks to some true angels. 

Today was one of the most life changing experiences, I can't wait to continue serving those in need and giving back to my community in a way more meaningful than I ever really imagined.

I'm so thankful to live this life, and to be in a position to give back, and to be able to pass on  the gift of giving back, with my children. 

P.A.L.S Co-op 1st Annual Thanksgiving dinner for those in need, down in the books! Thank you so much to my sweet friend Elyrha for introducing me to such a wonderful cause. My heart is so full. ❤️

Omg my grinch character really is me to a T. 💚

"I THINK THE SCHOOL SYSTEM, IS CRIMINAL, IN THAT IT KILLS A CHILD'S SPIRIT OF LEARNING." 

If you ever wondered what one of my biggest reasons behind homeschooling my littles was, THIS, this is it!!!

Imagine being a little bright eyed 3,4,5 year old, eager to start school for the first time, because it looks so fun. You hear so much about it from everyone around you, all the kids you know attend school, media and entertainment push the importance of school (not education), it's basically all you know. 

So you show up, an impressionable child, with the world at your fingertips, a lifetime of expectations, goals, learning, just to be told, "stay in your seat, no talking, single file line, no this isn't how you do it, it's done this way, the RIGHT way." 

NO THANK YOU!! 

Education is meant to be fun, exciting, intriguing,  you should WANT to be educated on the things you're interested in, not discouraged and pushed away. Education should encourage you to continue learning about what you're most passionate about. A burnout is less likely to happen when you're learning based off your interests, not what you're forced to.
Where's the lie though? 🤷🏻‍♀️
Merry Christmas to you and yours, from me and mine. 💚🎄❤️
Respectfully 👉🏻👈🏻🤷🏻‍♀️
